modules.description: This module handles input/output operations with channels, files, and standard streams, providing functions to read from and write to channels safely, copy data between streams, and manage temporary files or pipes. It supports in-channel, out-channel, buffer, and string data types, enabling tasks like capturing output, redirecting input, or streaming file contents. Specific use cases include reading a file into a string, copying a file to another location, redirecting standard input from a string, or capturing the output of a function into a buffer.
